Poland  rejected rapeseed cargoes
from Ukraine because of infestation with live and dead mites,
notifications to the European Unionâ€™s food-alert system showed.  A sample of Ukrainian rapeseed tested April 13 showed 20
mites for each kilogram (2.2 pounds) of the oilseed, while a
control check three days later found 80 mites a kilogram,
according to separate  notices  from Poland.  To contact the reporter on this story:
